    <h2>💎 What is Moss Agate?</h2>
    <p>
      Despite its name, moss agate is technically not a true agate, as it lacks the concentric banding. Instead, it is a form of chalcedony—a translucent quartz—filled with dendritic inclusions of manganese or iron that resemble moss, ferns, or forest scenes. This makes every stone completely unique, like a tiny world captured in crystal.
    </p>

