    <h2>⚒️ Moss Agate Durability & How to Care for It</h2>
    <p>
      Moss agate ranks around 6.5 to 7 on the Mohs hardness scale, which means it's durable enough for everyday wear with some care. Unlike diamonds or sapphires, it’s a softer stone that can scratch if worn carelessly or exposed to rough surfaces.
    </p>
    <p>
      We recommend choosing protective settings—like bezels or low-profile prongs—especially if the ring is meant for daily use. When not worn, store it in a soft cloth pouch or padded box, away from harder gemstones. Avoid ultrasonic cleaners and stick to gentle soap and water with a soft brush.
    </p>
    <p>
      With mindful handling, your moss agate jewelry will remain beautiful and full of meaning for many years to come.
    </p>

